	<h1>5 tips on naming your dev tool</h1>
	<h2>1. maximum 3 syllables, lesser the better
  <h2>2. Use food words (especially dryfruits, spices, dessert, and coffee drinks)
         mint pista mocha latte basil chilli eclair honey vanilla pepper gelato wasabi chestnut espresso cinnamon spearmint
  <h2>3. Use chemistry words
         ice acid atom neon oxide proton phospor kelvin crystal electron kinetic isotope
  <h3>4. Use color & light words
         red ruby rust lime blue azure amber olive chrome lumen chromatic indigo iridescent
  <h4>5. Use English words of Japanese origin (high-vowel content makes them easier to remember)
         zen sumo judo dojo ninja kendo emoji bento sensei samurai kaizen
  <h3>6. Combine words (with atleast one word related to your project)
         <a href="https://github.com/securelayer7/PinNinja">pin-ninja</a> (identify all UART pins with a single script)
         <a href="https://nimblebox.ai/">nimblebox</a> (out-of-the-box cloud environments)
         <a href="https://github.com/vologue/wafer">Wafer</a> (migration tool for AWS WAF)
         
Hope this helps! Thanks to itsron717 and nerdypepper for review.
